<main id="main-content" class="content-page">
  <div class="container">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">›</span><span>Cookie Policy</span></nav>
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Last updated: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) %></p>

    <h2>What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the site remember your preferences and improve your experience.</p>

    <h2>Cookies We Use</h2>

    <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
    <p>These are required for the game to function. They cannot be disabled.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>nickname</strong> — Remembers your display name (30-day expiry)</li>
      <li><strong>playerId</strong> — Allows reconnection to games (session-based)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
    <p>These help us understand how visitors use our site. They are only set with your consent.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>_ga</strong> — Google Analytics identifier (2-year expiry)</li>
      <li><strong>_gid</strong> — Google Analytics session (24-hour expiry)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Advertising Cookies</h3>
    <p>These are used to display relevant advertisements. They are only set with your consent.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>__gads</strong> — Google AdSense (13-month expiry)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Managing Cookies</h2>
    <p>You can manage your cookie preferences using the cookie consent banner that appears when you first visit the site. You can also clear cookies through your browser settings.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For questions about our cookie practices, email <a href="mailto:<%= supportEmail %>"><%= supportEmail %></a>.</p>
  </div>
</main>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
